<div class="comment-text">
<p>MichaelJ – You can have a large inheritance tax without abolishing inheritance.  After all, an inheritance is simply a large windfall income, and doesn’t even have to stay within a family.  The problem with current law is shown in the Trump inheritance (and mirrors most rich families) in which those with money and power can play the complex tax systems to their advantage, suggesting a simple (and to me fairer) system would much improve matters while reducing political corruption (when rich can pay for laws with enough wiggle room that they benefit a lot while most others may only benefit a little).</p>
