<div class="comment-text">
<p>@David: it was not my intention to come up with alternative communities compared to ours with their dynamic economic growth, but more as examples of egalitarian communities , as asked for by Ga. He thought that only negative feelings could be at stake there. Resentment and such ones. The ones I came with prove not so. As I said, for our modern, material way of life, the one we live with and are used to right now (I realise am also part of),they have little relevance. But I am sure, where anthropologists were seeking, many more such communities exist(ed).</p>
