<div class="comment-text">
<p>On top of this, there are more technical reasons why communism can never work. Prices in a free market system coordinate everything. They are an extraordinary source of information about what and how much to make. This is very important given the depth and complexity of supply chains, something someone who has never worked in industry will most likely not understand.</p>
<p>When a company is profitable, it’s a signal from the market saying ‘we’ve figured out that this is an arrangement of resources and inputs that efficiently delivers a product that consumers value’. (And the converse is a signal to give up and try something different). Without these signals, we are blind, and prosperity plummets. Profit is a Darwinian mechanism where only good investment survives.</p>
