<p>Agreed that probably most of the people in the west who regard themselves as socialists are not socialists in the sense used by this article. They just want more things to be socialised (e.g. healthcare in the US, trains in the UK) than is currently the case, and in particular they don’t want the “socialism for the rich and capitalism for the poor” that we often have in practice. </p>
